Zandile Christmas Mafe (C), a suspect in connection to a fire at the South African Parliament, appears at the Magistrate Court in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - Alleged Parliament arsonist Zandile Mafe was denied bail on Friday. The 49-year-old is facing charges relating to that devastating fire. READ: Parliament Fire | Mafe speaks out about mental illness stigma The Cape Town regional court was not satisfied that the applicant provided exceptional circumstances to be released on bail. He took the stand last Saturday during his bail hearing. The matter will return to Cape Town magistrate's court on 11 February.